cs.DC, cs.LO, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a likely category as the paper deals with networks of mobile agents communicating with each other. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the decidability and complexity of the synchronization problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the behavior of a system of agents following some communication topology. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of the synchronization problem under different constraints. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with formal models and verification of properties in a network of agents.
